   {
      "body" : "My point is just it can use system memory explicit way, and not to write to disk everytime it finished with one block. This definitely will be faster.\r\n\r\nIf you take ANY application, rewrite it so all the data that it uses will be on disk, not in memory, it will be I/O limited application then. But apperantly programmers\r\nsometimes use disk and sometimes memory, to avoid creating too many IO limited applications.\r\n",
